
[1]arthritis

   ARTHRIT'IS, n. [Gr. from a joint. It seems to be of the same family as
   artus, a limb.]

   In a general sense, any painful disease of the joints; but more
   particularly, the gout, an hereditary, intermitting disease, usually
   affecting the small joints; sometimes the stomach.
